to the editor the creation of embryos for research is opposed not only by religious conservatives and abortion opponents front page may 26 it is objectionable to many of us who support women 's reproductive freedom because it is a step toward commercial use of human embryos and another source of potential harm to women 's health there is no moral imperative to do embryonic stem cell research at this time and there are more promising ways to spend research dollars abby lippman montreal may 27 2002 the writer is a professor of medicine mcgill university

